  <dashboards>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Business Insight Summary'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q10. Business Insight Summary</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Insight 1: The Dominance of the West Region and Technology Sector</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Observation:</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Looking at the &quot;Regional Contribution Analysis&quot; and &quot;Category Performance Analysis,&quot; the West region leads in sales volume (287,787), while the East lags behind (242,025). Concurrently, &quot;Technology&quot; is the highest-grossing product category overall, closely followed by Furniture.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>How it helps management:</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Management can use this to optimize inventory and marketing. They should ensure distribution centers in the West are heavily stocked with Technology and Furniture items to support that high demand. Furthermore, they can initiate a targeted marketing campaign or promotional discounts specifically in the East region to boost sales and close the 45,000+ revenue gap.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Insight 2: Severe End-of-Period Sales Plunge</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Observation:</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> The &quot;Sales Trend Analysis&quot; line chart reveals that while sales maintain a relatively stable, fluctuating rhythm between ~60K and ~90K for the majority of the year, there is a drastic, near-vertical drop in sales immediately following the October/November period.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>How it helps management:</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> This is a critical red flag. Management must immediately investigate the cause of this cliff-edge drop. They need to determine if this is a recurring seasonal slump (e.g., people stop buying after a specific holiday), a stockout issue, or simply incomplete data for that final month. If it is a genuine historical drop in demand, the business needs to plan aggressive end-of-year clearance sales or heavy promotional events to stimulate buying during that specific downturn.</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='6' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98000' id='5' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q10. Business Insight Summary</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Insight 1: The Dominance of the West Region and Technology Sector</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Observation:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Looking at the &quot;Regional Contribution Analysis&quot; and &quot;Category Performance Analysis,&quot; the West region leads in sales volume (287,787), while the East lags behind (242,025). Concurrently, &quot;Technology&quot; is the highest-grossing product category overall, closely followed by Furniture.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>How it helps management:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Management can use this to optimize inventory and marketing. They should ensure distribution centers in the West are heavily stocked with Technology and Furniture items to support that high demand. Furthermore, they can initiate a targeted marketing campaign or promotional discounts specifically in the East region to boost sales and close the 45,000+ revenue gap.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Insight 2: Severe End-of-Period Sales Plunge</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Observation:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> The &quot;Sales Trend Analysis&quot; line chart reveals that while sales maintain a relatively stable, fluctuating rhythm between ~60K and ~90K for the majority of the year, there is a drastic, near-vertical drop in sales immediately following the October/November period.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>How it helps management:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> This is a critical red flag. Management must immediately investigate the cause of this cliff-edge drop. They need to determine if this is a recurring seasonal slump (e.g., people stop buying after a specific holiday), a stockout issue, or simply incomplete data for that final month. If it is a genuine historical drop in demand, the business needs to plan aggressive end-of-year clearance sales or heavy promotional events to stimulate buying during that specific downturn.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
