    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Chart Selection Justification'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='9' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <zone h='98000' id='7' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
              <zone h='98000' id='5' type-v2='layout-basic' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q9. Chart Selection Justification</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>Explain why different charts were used for different business questions in this analysis.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Bar Charts (Task 1):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Used for categorical comparison. The length of the bar easily allows the human eye to compare the total sales volume across different categories and rank them from highest to lowest.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Line Charts (Tasks 2 &amp; 5):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> The best practice for time-series data. Connecting data points with a line emphasizes the continuity of time, making it easy to spot peaks, valleys, and overall directional trends (like cumulative growth).</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Pie Charts (Task 3):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Used specifically because the business need asked for &quot;contribution&quot; to a whole. A pie chart visually represents a part-to-whole relationship perfectly.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Scatter Plots (Tasks 4 &amp; 7):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Essential for showing the correlation and relationship between two continuous numerical variables (Sales and Profit). It allows us to easily spot outliers (e.g., high sales but negative profit).</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Highlight Table (Task 6):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Cross-tabulating two categories (Region and Category) using a highlight table allows for quick visual scanning to find hot spots (dark colors for high sales) and cold spots (light colors for low sales) in a matrix format.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='11' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98000' id='10' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q9. Chart Selection Justification</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>Explain why different charts were used for different business questions in this analysis.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Bar Charts (Task 1):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Used for categorical comparison. The length of the bar easily allows the human eye to compare the total sales volume across different categories and rank them from highest to lowest.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Line Charts (Tasks 2 &amp; 5):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> The best practice for time-series data. Connecting data points with a line emphasizes the continuity of time, making it easy to spot peaks, valleys, and overall directional trends (like cumulative growth).</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Pie Charts (Task 3):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Used specifically because the business need asked for &quot;contribution&quot; to a whole. A pie chart visually represents a part-to-whole relationship perfectly.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Scatter Plots (Tasks 4 &amp; 7):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Essential for showing the correlation and relationship between two continuous numerical variables (Sales and Profit). It allows us to easily spot outliers (e.g., high sales but negative profit).</run>
